metadata.name: Possible Ways #166
metadata.description:
This project is written in javascript without using any other libraries, and it is an endless real-time software animation.

The appearance of each token is initially determined by the hash, but the size and positions of its elements change randomly over time, creating an infinite performance.

While working on this project, I was inspired by the elusiveness of the moment, that cannot be saved or predicted. It can only be experienced.

metadata.name: Curlida #110
metadata.description:
Fully generative art. Each token is 100% unique.

Traits:
- 28 color palettes;
- 5 "stylers" - cells filling style;
- 3 "ratio" - aspect ratio.

Press 's' to save png.

High-level description of the algorithm:
Frame is separated into flows using several different Perlin noise generators. 
Frame cells are filled with curves. Each curve is drawn in the direction plotted by noise generator.
Each value returned by the generator at (x, y) is mapped to color from a predefined range.


Made with p5js, math and love by @ivposure

metadata.name: Sound Therapy #108
metadata.description:
[ CLICK TO START THE SOUND ]

Best viewed on a decent GPU for 60fps rendering
Play the instrument by moving, clicking & dragging your cursor / finger

The combination of real-time graphics and generative music has always fascinated me, and what could be a better addition to the mix than a physics library for creating playful instruments. The instrument will play itself with a predefined pattern, but you can take over the controls and immerse yourself in the sound therapy. Enjoy and relax!

Keyboard
[ space ] - pause
[ s ] - save image
[ f ] - full screen

Mobile
[ two finger tap ] - pause

Created with Three.js + rapier.js
Copyright (c) June-July 2022 Shaderism

metadata.name: Primordial #35
metadata.description:
Primordial is a study of abstract forms. The algorithm, written in p5.js and WebGL, utilizes domain warping to create twisted fields of color and then overlays thousands of tiny lines to provide depth and texture. The outputs are chaotic but not completely formless, like a swirling mass of plasma from the early universe, or a strange proto-life form suspended in prehistoric ooze.

CONTROLS:

1-9: Increase resolution and save image in PNG format

B: Toggle borders on/off

F: Fullscreen
P: Portrait
L: Landscape
S: Square

For third party license information, please see license.md

David Brice Allen
October 2022

metadata.name: GEN XYZ Das Occult #1506
metadata.description:
A 10k Generative Profile Pic collection
GEN XYZ Das Occult - by culla - @tamccullough

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes
A selection of rare palettes
And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes
However, rarity will be based on what combinations the code produces

The majority of tokens will not have a special trait
However your token might have one or even multiple special traits
But, be aware that only the last special trait added will be listed in the features

Even then, look closely, because not all aspects of the canvas are included in the features. Collectors should still look closely and choose what they like when buying on secondary.

Which team are you on? X or O?

follow culla on twitter for updates. Or maybe __acolyte__

If the non reserved tokens mint out quickly, Access List mints will have 24 hours to mint reserves assigned to those wallets

Thank you for supporting an emerging artist in the generative art space

Access List reserves were given to holders of the following PFP collections created by culla
2x for each Basqunk held
1x for each Inkspunk, TwoFourQunk, V0iD, DeeManz, Punkasso and CR0$$KULL
You would have needed to transfer the above tokens to your mint wallet at the time of the snapshot

share your tokens on social media with #genxyznft
Made with love by culla using p5.js

metadata.name: Crece #6
metadata.description:
¿Cuál es la forma de la metáfora? - What is the shape of the metaphor?


Crece (It grows) is the manifestation of the metaphor in relation to materiality and abstraction.
Only sensations that escape the everyday. The time in which it is built and grows, shows and hides ungraspable instants. In any case: What shape would the metaphor take before it grew or manifested?

This project is based on the investigation of the algorithm used in "99 recorridos" and has to do with three questions, the animated effect of growth of the drawing that resembles roots as in "99 recorridos", but in this case it does not evoke the natural, but the artificial with the inclusion of harsher, straighter lines that is more closely to sci-fi imagery. Second, it has to do with the growth of the algorithm, from new lines of code that give it its personality. Thirdly, a metaphorical, imaginary and internal growth that arises from that dialogue that enriches our souls in this coexistence.

Playing with features:

-Oldness of the metaphor
-Growth impulse of the shape
-Growth duration
-Pigmentary composition of the metaphor
-Rhizome
-Shape of the metaphor
-The moment


Crece es la manifestación de la metáfora en relación con la materialidad y la abstracción.
Solo sensaciones que se escapan a lo cotidiano. El tiempo en que se construye y crece, muestra y oculta instantes inasibles. En todo caso: ¿Qué forma tendría la metáfora antes de crecer o de manifestarse? 

Este proyeco parte de la investigación del algoritmo utilizado en 99 recorridos y tiene que ver con tres cuestiones, el efecto animado de crecimiento del dibujo que se asemeja a raíces como en 99 recorridos, pero en este caso no evoca lo natural, sino lo artificial con la inclusión de líneas más duras y rectas que se asemejan más al imaginario sci-fi. Por otra parte, tiene que ver con un crecimiento del algoritmo, a partir de nuevas líneas de código que van dando su personalidad. En tercer lugar, un crecimiento metafórico, imaginario e interno, que surge de ese diálogo que nos enriquece el alma en esta convivencia.

Jugando con los atributos:

-Vejez de la matafora
-Impulso de crecimiento de la metafora
-Duracion del crecimiento
-Composicion pigmentaria de la metafora
-Rizoma
-Forma de la metafora
-El momento


Keys:

[1,2,3] -> change pixel density. Be aware for the file size in render. (Or can be passed via url ?pd= different numbers)
[s] -> download canvas capture. Different pixel density, different sizes.
[double tap] -> download canvas capture on mobile
[L] -> (loop/noLoop) what happens if it doesn't stop?

metadata.name: Midfile Crisis #114
metadata.description:
Midfile Crisis is about realizing halfway through you are not gonna make it.

The struggle is real.

-

The work itself is the union of 2 projects, which, well, didn’t make it. Together though, they are stronger than ever. So yes, Midfile Crisis is a love story, too.

-

Procedural , ever changing real-time animation, October 2022
Javascript and WebGL

-

FEATURES

- 6 color palettes, inspired by recent artworks by Xenia Hausner, Ayako Rokkaku, Jenny Saville, Amy Sherald, Sue Williams and Emily Xie, are referenced accordingly. One additional, rare color palette will slowly cycle through the full color spectrum.
- Direction: Up, Right, Up Right
- Seed: Up, Right, Up Left
- Shape Tendency: Tetra, Box, Sphere, Octa, Ico, Multi
- Amount: Low, Medium, High

VIEWING

- The artwork is in landscape format, please click on open to see the full frame and resolution. We recommend rotating your screen on mobile.
- Press 'i' to show artwork title and features.
- Press 's' to save an image.
- To guarantee the same output at different resolutions the simulation driving the artwork is locked at 1024x512 pixels. To unlock, press 'u' - this can help when running at a lower resolution and the animation is not smooth, or when running at significanly higher resolutions and pixelation is starting to occur. Please note this will break the deterministic nature of the work.
- Best viewed in Chrome Desktop with dedicated GPU.
- Please note: requires latest devices (supporting WebGL2) for a smooth experience.
